{{Infobox monument | image = The Prime Minister, Shri Narendra Modi inaugurating the Dr. Ambedkar National Memorial at 26 Alipur Road, Delhi on April 13, 2018.jpg | caption = The Prime Minister, [[Narendra Modi]] inaugurating the Dr. Ambedkar National Memorial at 26 Alipur Road, Delhi on April 13, 2018 | location = 26 Alipur Road, [[Delhi]], India | designer = | type = Monument and museum | material = | length = | width = | height = | begin = {{start date|df=y|2016|03|21}} | complete = 2018 | open = {{end date and age|df=y|2018|04|13}} | dedicated_to = [[Babasaheb Ambedkar]] | map_name = | map_caption = | coordinates = | website = }}
The '''Dr. Ambedkar National Memorial''' or the '''Dr. Ambedkar Mahaparinirvana Sthal''' is a museum and memorial dedicated to [[B. R. Ambedkar|Babasaheb Ambedkar]] at 26, Alipur Road in [[Delhi]]. On 13 April 2018, the 127th [[Ambedkar Jayanti|birth anniversary of Babasaheb Ambedkar]], India's Prime Minister [[Narendra Modi]] inaugurated the memorial. This is the place where Ambedkar breathed his last or attained ''Mahaparinirvana'' on 6 December 1956.<ref>{{Cite news|url=https://m.timesofindia.com/india/pm-modi-inaugurates-dr-ambedkar-national-memorial-highlights/articleshow/63750403.cms|title=PM Modi inaugurates Dr Ambedkar National Memorial: Highlights - Times of India|work=The Times of India|access-date=2018-11-13}}</ref><ref>{{Cite web|url=https://thewire.in/the-arts/ambedkar-memorial-delhi|title=Ambedkar Memorial Gets Final Touches Ahead of Inauguration by Modi|website=The Wire|access-date=2018-11-13}}</ref>
==History== [[File:Dr. Bhimrao Ambedkar.jpg|right|thumb|The memorial is dedicated to [[B. R. Ambedkar]].]] Bhimrao Ramji Ambedkar was born on 14 April 1891 at [[Mhow]] (now [[Dr. Ambedkar Nagar]]) in [[Madhya Pradesh]] and was the first [[Minister of Law and Justice]] of Independent India. After resigning from the Union Cabinet on 1st November 1951, Ambedkar started residing in the house of Maharaja of Sirohi at 26, Alipur Road, Delhi where he breathed his last and attained [[Parinirvana|Mahaparinirvana]] on 6th December 1956. In the memory of Babasaheb Ambedkar, ''Dr. Ambedkar Mahaparinirvana Sthal'', 26, Alipur Road was dedicated to the Nation by [[Atal Bihari Vajpayee]], the then Prime Minister of India on 2nd December, 2003. Ambedkarites, the followers of Babasaheb believe 26, Alipur Road as Holy place where he attained Mahaparinirvana. Since this building was to be constructed as a Memorial of Babasaheb, who was the brain behind the [[Constitution of India]], hence, the building has been given the shape of a book (the ''Constitution of India''). The Foundation stone of the memorial was laid by the India's Prime Minister [[Narendra Modi]] on 21 March, 2016. On 13 April 2018, the eve of the 127th [[Ambedkar Jayanti|birth anniversary of Babasaheb Ambedkar]], PM [[Narendra Modi]] inaugurated Dr. Ambedkar National Memorial at 26, Alipur Road in Delhi.<ref>{{Cite news|url=https://m.dailyhunt.in/news/india/english/news+bharati-epaper-newsbhar/read+here+to+know+about+dr+ambedkar+national+memorial+pm+modi+gifts+the+epitome+for+world+to+inspire+and+contribute+towards+society-newsid-85701140|title=Read here to know about Dr Ambedkar National Memorial: PM Modi gifts the 'epitome' for world to inspire and contribute towards society - News Bharati {{!}} DailyHunt|work=DailyHunt|access-date=2018-11-13|language=en}}</ref><ref>{{Cite news|url=https://www.bhaskar.com/union-territory/new-delhi/news/UT-DEL-HMU-NEW-LCL-bhaskar-special-report-on-dr-br-ambedkar-national-memorial-5841462-PHO.html|title=3D में अंबेडकर को सुनेंगे ‘लाइव’, घूमते हुए दिखेंगे, टच बटन से पलटेंगे संविधान के पन्ने|work=Dainik Bhaskar|access-date=2018-11-13|language=hi}}</ref><ref>{{Cite news|url=https://m.navbharattimes.indiatimes.com/india/prime-minister-narendra-modi-dedicated-dr-ambedkar-national-memorial-to-the-nation/articleshow/63749507.cms|title=PM मोदी ने आंबेडकर स्मारक का उद्घाटन किया-Navbharat Times|work=Navbharat Times|access-date=2018-11-13|language=hi-IN}}</ref>
==Structures== [[File:The Vice President, Shri M. Venkaiah Naidu paying floral tributes to Dr. B.R. Ambedkar, at the Dr. Ambedkar National Memorial, in Delhi.JPG|thumb|Ambedkar bust in the memorial, The Vice President, M. Venkaiah Naidu paying floral tributes to B.R. Ambedkar]]
The memorial is spread over an area of approx. 7400 square meters and built at a cost of ₹100 [[Crore|crores]]. The memorial is completely green building. First building in the country with facade of open book which reflects the constitution of Indian. The memorial has an advanced museum, in which the life and works of B. R. Ambedkar are shown through modern technology. The building has an exhibition area, memorial, meditation hall with the [[Gautama Buddha]] Statue, 12 feet height bronze statue of Ambedkar among others. Ashok Stambh [[Pillars of Ashoka|Ashoka Pillar]] (11 m) at Entrance Plaza and Meditation Hall at Back side has been constructed. There exists Sewerage Treatment Plant (30 KLD), Rain Water Harvesting System and roof top solar energy (50 kw) with net metering. The building stands in plot area of 7374 sq meter and a total built up area of 6758 sq meter.<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://abpnews.abplive.in/india-news/ambedkar-national-memorial-where-br-ambedkar-took-his-last-breathe-832682/amp|title=अंबेडकर राष्ट्रीय स्मारक: जहां संविधान रचयिता ने ली थी आखिरी सांस|last=न्यूज़|first=अंकित गुप्ता, संवाददाता, एबीपी|website=ABP News|language=hi-IN|access-date=2018-11-13}}</ref><ref>{{Cite news|url=https://m.jagranjosh.com/current-affairs/pm-modi-inaugurates-dr-ambedkar-national-memorial-in-hindi-1523699075-2|title=प्रधानमंत्री नरेन्द्र मोदी ने डॉ. अम्बेडकर राष्ट्रीय स्मारक का उद्घाटन किया|date=2018-04-14|work=Jagranjosh.com|access-date=2018-11-13}}</ref> The museum at the memorial intends to create an immersive experience into the life of Ambedkar and his contribution to India through extensive use of static media, dynamic media, audio-visual content and multimedia technologies," a release had said earlier. A meditation hall has also been created. A [[Bodhi Tree]], a musical fountain and a facade lighting are the other attractions of the memorial.<ref>{{Cite news|url=https://m.timesofindia.com/city/delhi/pm-modi-takes-delhi-metro-ride-to-dedicate-ambedkar-national-memorial-to-nation/articleshow/63749235.cms|title=PM Modi takes Delhi Metro ride to dedicate Ambedkar National Memorial to nation - Times of India|work=The Times of India|access-date=2018-11-13}}</ref> * Bhim Stambh (Bhim/Ambedkar pillar) * Musical fountains, a replica of the Ashoka pillar at Sarnath and a 12 foot high bronze statue are some of the highlights of this complex. * The first floor houses high quality displays related to Babasaheb's life. The lower level of the two-storied building has an exhibition gallery, where days spent by Ambedkar on the premises have been illustrated. His last days and journey have also been captured vividly. * There are also virtual reality displays of Babasaheb giving finishing touches to the Constitution of India. * And this unique interactive table is a delight for Constitution lovers. It is full of information on Babasaheb Ambedkar and the Indian Constitution. * The Memorial also has a meditation hall with a Marble statue of the Buddha. The stone used is from [[Vietnam]].<ref>{{Cite web|url=http://ddnews.gov.in/national/pm-modi-iaugurates-dr-ambedkar-national-memorial-26-alipur-road-new-delhi|title=PM Modi iaugurates Dr Ambedkar National Memorial at 26 Alipur Road in New Delhi {{!}} DD News|website=ddnews.gov.in|language=en|access-date=2018-11-13}}</ref><ref>{{Cite web|url=http://ddnews.gov.in/national/pm-modi-inaugurate-dr-ambedkar-national-memorial-delhi|title=PM Modi to inaugurate Dr Ambedkar National Memorial in Delhi {{!}} DD News|website=ddnews.gov.in|language=en|access-date=2018-11-13}}</ref>
