According to the 2010 census, Evangelicals comprised 2% of the population, however 2010 surveys and data such Joshua Project and Operation World estimated the evangelical population to be around 11–13% of the population.<ref>{{Cite web|url=http://www.operationworld.org/phil|title=Philippines {{!}} Operation World|website=www.operationworld.org|language=en|access-date=2017-02-09|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20170211075916/http://www.operationworld.org/phil#|archive-date=2017-02-11|dead-url=no|df=}}</ref>  It is particularly strong among American and Korean communities, Northern Luzon especially in [[Cordillera Administrative Region]], [[Soccsksargen|Southern Mindanao]]<ref>{{Cite web|url=http://philchal.org/dawn/nationalsum.asp?usersort=perev_desc|title=Philippine Church National Summary|website=philchal.org|access-date=2017-09-17|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20170917213510/http://philchal.org/dawn/nationalsum.asp?usersort=perev_desc#|archive-date=2017-09-17|dead-url=no|df=}}</ref> and many other tribal groups in the Philippines.<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://joshuaproject.net/countries/RP|title=Philippines :: Joshua Project|last=Project|first=Joshua|website=joshuaproject.net|language=en|access-date=2017-02-09|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20170808004027/https://joshuaproject.net/countries/RP#|archive-date=2017-08-08|dead-url=no|df=}}</ref> Protestants both mainline and evangelical have gained significant annual growth rate up to 10% since 1910 to 2015.<ref>{{Cite web|url=http://www.gordonconwell.edu/shared-content-temp-research/documents/236e0d3b6-d706-4bcf-a892-87a608c59104-18.pdf|title=500 years of Protestantism(World Christian Database)|last=|first=|date=|website=|access-date=|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20170218145254/http://www.gordonconwell.edu/shared-content-temp-research/documents/236e0d3b6-d706-4bcf-a892-87a608c59104-18.pdf#|archive-date=2017-02-18|dead-url=no|df=}}</ref>

