{{Infobox academic|name=Veli-Matti Kärkkäinen|birth_date={{birth year and age|1958}}|birth_place=Finland|occupation=Professor|alma_mater=[[University of Helsinki]], [[Fuller Theological Seminary]], [[University of Jyväskylä]]|discipline=[[Systematic Theology]]|workplaces=[[Fuller Theological Seminary]]}}
'''Veli-Matti Kärkkäinen''' (born 1958) is a Finnish theologian. He is Professor of [[Systematic theology|Systematic Theology]] at [[Fuller Theological Seminary]]. An ordained Lutheran minister (ELCA - Evangelical Lutheran Church in America), he is also a world-renowned expert on Pentecostal-Charismatic theologies.
== Biography == Veli-Matti Kärkkäinen was born into a Finnish [[Lutheranism|Lutheran]] family. As a teenager, he would eventually become affiliated to a local Pentecostal church in his homeland.<ref name=":0" /> Later in life, he has been ordained as minister of ELCA and serves as part-time associate pastor for Finnish Lutheran Church in California and Texas (under Southwest California ELCA synod).
After receiving a [[Master of Education|M.Ed.]] from the [[University of Jyväskylä]], Kärkkäinen pursued a [[Master of Arts|M.A.]] in theology from Fuller Theological Seminary. He returned to Finland and was ordained as a minister of the [[Full Gospel Church]] of Finland, pastoring a local congregation from 1989-1991. In 1991, he moved his family to [[Thailand]] and taught at the Full Gospel Bible College in [[Bangkok]]. Three years later he return to Finland, becoming president of the [[Iso Kirja Bible College]] in [[Keuruu]] in 1994. He completed his doctorate at the [[University of Helsinki]] in 1998.<ref name=":0" /><ref>{{cite web|url=http://humbleapproach.templeton.org/Pneumatology/participants/karkk.html|title=Participants|website=Humble Approach Initiative|publisher=[[John Templeton Foundation]]|accessdate=6 March 2016}}</ref><ref name=":1">{{cite web|title=Veli-Matti Kärkkäinen|url=http://fuller.edu/faculty/v-mkarkkainen/|publisher=[[Fuller Theological Seminary]]|accessdate=6 March 2016}}</ref>
Karkkainen join the faculty of Fuller in 2000 as [[associate professor]] of [[systematic theology]] and became [[Professor (highest academic rank)|full professor]] in 2003.<ref name=":1" /> Kärkkäinen also serves as [[Docent]] of Ecumenics at the [[University of Helsinki]].<ref>{{cite web|url=http://cct.biola.edu/about/veli-matti-karkkainen/|title=Veli-Matti Kärkkäinen|publisher=[[Biola University]]|accessdate=6 March 2016}}</ref>
== Theology == Kärkkäinen has written textbooks offering global introductions to [[pneumatology]], [[ecclesiology]], and [[christology]].
In 2017 he completed the fifth of his projected five-volume systematic theology series called ''Constructive Christian Theology for the Church in the Pluralistic World'', which engages questions of [[Relationship between religion and science|science and religion]], [[World Christianity|global theology]], and [[Christianity and other religions|dialogue with other religions]] through [[comparative theology]].<ref>{{Cite book|url=https://books.google.com/books?id=EsM28Yhbt3MC|title=Christ and Reconciliation: A Constructive Christian Theology for the Pluralistic World|last=Kärkkäinen|first=Veli-Matti|date=2013|publisher=Wm. B. Eerdmans Publishing|year=|isbn=9780802868534|location=Grand Rapids, MI|pages=|language=en|via=}}</ref><ref>{{Cite book|url=https://books.google.com/books?id=aybpAgAAQBAJ|title=Trinity and Revelation: A Constructive Christian Theology for the Pluralistic World|last=Kärkkäinen|first=Veli-Matti|date=2014|publisher=Wm. B. Eerdmans Publishing|year=|isbn=9780802868541|location=Grand Rapids, MI|pages=|language=en|via=}}</ref><ref>{{Cite book|url=https://books.google.com/books?id=WpeVBgAAQBAJ|title=Creation and Humanity: A Constructive Christian Theology for the Pluralistic World|last=Kärkkäinen|first=Veli-Matti|date=2015|publisher=Wm. B. Eerdmans Publishing|year=|isbn=9780802868558|location=Grand Rapids, MI|pages=|language=en|via=}}</ref><ref>{{Cite book|url=https://books.google.com/books?id=EIy9CwAAQBAJ|title=Spirit and Salvation: A Constructive Christian Theology for the Pluralistic World|last=Kärkkäinen|first=Veli-Matti|date=2016|publisher=Wm. B. Eerdmans Publishing|year=|isbn=9780802868565|location=Grand Rapids, MI|pages=|language=en|via=}}</ref>
According to [[Amos Yong]], he is "fast becoming one of the more important theologians to be reckoned with in our time."<ref name=":0">{{cite book|url=https://books.google.com/books?id=L8_wCAAAQBAJ&pg=PA121|title=The Dialogical Spirit: Christian Reason and Theological Method in the Third Millennium|last=Yong|first=Amos|author-link=Amos Yong|publisher=James Clark and Co.|year=2015|isbn=|location=Cambridge|pages=121-148|chapter=Whither Evangelical Theology? The Work of Veli-Matti Kärkkäinen as a Case Study of Contemporary Trajectories|via=}}</ref>
Main works: * {{Cite book|ref=harv|last=Kärkkäinen|first=Veli-Matti|authorlink=Veli-Matti Kärkkäinen|title=Pneumatology: The Holy Spirit in Ecumenical, International, and Contextual Perspective|year=2002|location=Grand Rapids, MI|publisher=Baker Academic|url=https://books.google.com/books?id=XI6iB7Cry6AC}} * {{Cite book|ref=harv|last=Kärkkäinen|first=Veli-Matti|authorlink=Veli-Matti Kärkkäinen|title=The Doctrine of God: A Global Introduction|year=2004|location=Grand Rapids, MI|publisher=Baker Academic|url=https://books.google.com/books?id=IfygBeFoldcC}} * {{Cite book|ref=harv|editor-last=Kärkkäinen|editor-first=Veli-Matti|editor-link=Veli-Matti Kärkkäinen|title=Holy Spirit and Salvation: The Sources of Christian Theology|year=2010|location=Louisville, KY|publisher=Westminster John Knox Press|url=https://books.google.com/books?id=buA7YKLWe6YC}}
